Ahmad Lawan was elected and sworn in as the Senate president of Nigeria on Tuesday, June 11 when the Ninth National Assembly was inaugurated with 79 votes to beat Senator Ali Ndume with 28 votes.
Here are seven quick facts to know about him: *He became a Senator in 2007 and was the immediate Senate Leader of the 8th Assembly. *He is the most experienced Senator in the ranks of the All Progressive Congress (APC) having been elected for fourth successive term. *In 2008, he was a member of the National Assemblyâ€™s Joint Committee on Constitution Review.